00:08:49.472 --> 00:08:51.647
The Bill and Melinda Gates Foundation

00:08:51.647 --> 00:08:53.927
and from Google and other private donors.

00:08:53.927 --> 00:08:55.257
Tom: $1.5 million from Bill Gates.

00:08:55.257 --> 00:08:56.967
I think something like $6 million in total

00:08:56.967 --> 00:08:57.963
has come your way now.

00:08:58.316 --> 00:09:01.451
Khan: Yes, yes. And so, we
have a team of 14 people.

00:09:01.451 --> 00:09:03.380
I'd say about two-thirds of those people

00:09:03.380 --> 00:09:04.652
are focused on the software side.

00:09:04.652 --> 00:09:07.152
Khan Academy now is, the videos are there

00:09:07.152 --> 00:09:09.468
and that's probably
where most people's first

00:09:09.468 --> 00:09:11.969
experience happens, but
what we're trying to do

00:09:11.969 --> 00:09:14.221
is turn it into a full,
for lack of a better word,

00:09:14.221 --> 00:09:15.751
virtual school where anyone can go there.

00:09:15.751 --> 00:09:18.303
They have the videos on
demand, but they also

00:09:18.303 --> 00:09:20.051
have exercises and the
exercises start them

00:09:20.051 --> 00:09:21.129
at basic addtion.

00:09:21.129 --> 00:09:22.884
There's these game mechanics around it.

00:09:22.884 --> 00:09:25.352
It keeps track of their
progress, gives them feedback.

00:09:25.352 --> 00:09:27.796
If they have a teacher
or a parent that can act

00:09:27.796 --> 00:09:29.800
as a coach, it can give them
data and analytics on it

00:09:29.800 --> 00:09:33.050
and so, the idea is, if you have nothing,

00:09:33.050 --> 00:09:34.952
if all you have is access to the site,

00:09:34.952 --> 00:09:36.978
you can get a pretty solid grounding

00:09:36.978 --> 00:09:39.908
in a lot of core concepts and if you do

00:09:39.908 --> 00:09:42.250
have access to a teacher,
this has the potential

00:09:42.250 --> 00:09:44.468
